    <p>• Fungi pro­tein found in vol­canic hot springs</p>
    <p>• A mi­crobe fungi, Fusar­ium strain flavolapis, was ex­tracted from the hot springs of Yel­low­stone Na­tional Park</p>
    <p>• Fer­men­ta­tion is used to con­vert it into a pro­tein, called Fy, which is har­vested into a solid, liq­uid or pow­der that can be used in food and drinks</p>
    <p>• The Fy pro­tein con­tains all 20 amino acids</p>
    <p>Progress</p>
    <p>• The com­pany be­gan pro­duc­tion early this year at its fac­tory in Chicago</p>
    <p>• It is plan­ning to pro­duce “a ham­burger equiv­a­lent” next year</p>
    <p>Na­ture’s Fynd’s CEO Thomas Jonas fold­ing the Fy pro­tein</p>

